===Usage Note===

Strictly, the past tense of [[hang]] is [[hanged]] for the second meaning (to suspend from the neck until dead) and [[hung]] for all other meanings. However, this rule is not uniformly understood or observed; [[hung]] is sometimes substituted for [[hanged]] or (more rarely) vice versa.

